    "explanation": "<p>Solid models in CAD are built up by defining and linking their faces, edges and vertices—that’s exactly what boundary representation (B-rep) does.  </p>\n<p>• Option A (B-rep) is the solid-modeling method.  </p>\n<p>• Options B, C and D (Bézier, B-splines, NURBS) are mathematical ways to represent curves and surfaces, which you then use as faces in a B-rep model.</p>",
