    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The correct choice is Option B: ultrasonic machining.  </p>\n<p>Why ultrasonic machining works best for ceramics and glass:  </p>\n\n<p><p>Both ceramics and glass are hard, brittle, and electrically non-conductive.  </p></p>\n<p><p>Ultrasonic machining uses a vibrating tool and an abrasive slurry to wear away material by micro-chipping.  </p></p>\n<p><p>No need for electrical conductivity (unlike EDM or ECM), and it avoids the high thermal stresses of plasma processes.</p></p>\n",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "gate-me-2025",
    "difficulty": null
  },
