    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The preparatory functions in Computer Numerical Controlled (CNC) machine programming are denoted by the alphabet \"G\". These \"G-codes\" are used to prepare the machine for different functions and operations, such as moving to a specific position, starting and stopping the spindle, and other essential tasks required before executing the actual machining commands.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Option A:</strong> G</p>\n\n<p><strong>Option B:</strong> M</p>\n\n<p><strong>Option C:</strong> P</p>\n\n<p><strong>Option D:</strong> O</p>\n\n<p>Therefore, the correct answer is <strong>Option A: G</strong>.</p>",
